  body "û}}, {{tt+|wa|a}}, {{tt+|wa|diewåde}} {{qualifier|old}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|helo}}, {{tt|cy|bore da}} {{qualifier|good morning}}, {{tt|cy|dydd da}} {{qualifier|good day}}, {{tt|cy|hylo}}\n* Winnebago: "
  body "{{tt|win|haho}} {{qualifier|male speaker}}, {{tt|win|hą}} {{qualifier|female speaker}}, {{tt|win|hinįkaraginʼ}}\n* Xhosa: {{tt|xh|molo|s}}, {{tt|xh|molweni|p}}\n* Xibe: {{tt|sjo|ᠪᠠᡳᡨᠠᡴᡡ ᠨᠠ|tr=baitakū "
  body "na}}\n* Yakut: {{tt|sah|эҕэрдэ}}, {{tt|sah|дорообо}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Yiddish: {{tt|yi|שלום־עליכם|tr=sholem-aleykhem}}, {{tt+|yi|אַ גוטן}}, {{tt+|yi|גוט־מאָרגן}}\n* Yoruba: {{tt|yo|[[pẹ̀lẹ́|ẹ"
  body " pẹ̀lẹ́]]}} {{q|polite}}, {{tt|yo|pẹ̀lẹ́}} {{q|non-polite}}\n* Yup'ik: {{tt|esu|waqaa}}, {{tt|esu|cama-i}}\n* Zapotec:\n*: Isthmus Zapotec: {{tt|zai|ola}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt|zza|sılam}}, {{tt|zza|namaste"
  body "}}\n* Zhuang: {{tt|za|mwngz ndei}}\n* Zulu: {{tt+|zu|sawubona}} {{qualifier|familiar}}, {{tt|zu|sanibonani}} {{qualifier|plural|respectful}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|when answering the tel"
  body "ephone}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|hallo}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|alo}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|آلُو}}, {{tt|ar|آلُوْ}}, {{tt+|ar|أَلُو}}, {{tt+|ar|أَلُوْ}}\n*: Gulf Arabic: {{tt|afb|اَلُو|tr"
  body "=alū}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|ألو|tr=ʔalu}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{tt|aii|ܐܲܠܘܼ}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|ալլո}}\n* Assamese: {{tt|as|হেল’}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt|az|alo}}\n* Bashkir"
  body ": {{tt|ba|алло}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|алё}}\n* Bengali: {{tt+|bn|হ্যালো}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt|bg|а́ло}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|အမိန့်ရှိပါ}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|digui}}, {{tt+|ca|si}}, {{tt+|ca|hola}}"
  body ", {{tt|ca|mani'm}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt|yue|喂|tr=wai2, wei2}}\n*: Hakka: {{tt|hak|摩西摩西|tr=mò-si-mo-sí}}, {{tt|hak|噯|tr=ói}}\n*: Hokkien: {{tt+|nan-hbl|喂|tr=oeh}}\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|喂|t"
  body "r=wéi}}\n*: Wu: {{tt|wuu|喂}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|haló}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|hallo}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|met|lit=with}} {{q|followed by name}}, {{t+|nl|tot|lit=to}} {{q|followed by name; Suriname}}, {{tt+"
  body "|nl|hallo}} {{q|rare on landlines, now chiefly for unknown caller IDs on mobile phones}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|halo}}\n* Estonian: {{tt+|et|hallo}}, {{tt+|et|halloo}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|haloo}}\n* F"
  body "rench: {{tt+|fr|allô}}\n* Frisian:\n*: West Frisian: {{tt|fy|hallo}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|diga}}\n* Georgian: {{tt|ka|ალო}}, {{tt|ka|გისმენთ}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|hallo}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|εμπρός}},"
  body " {{tt+|el|παρακαλώ}}, {{tt+|el|ναι;}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t|haw|ō}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|שָׁלוֹם?|tr=shalóm?}}, {{tt|he|הָלוֹ?|tr=haló?}}\n* Hindi: {{tt|hi|हलो}}, {{tt|hi|हैलो}}, {{tt+|hi|हेलो}}\n* Hungaria"
  body "n: {{tt+|hu|halló}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt+|is|halló}}, {{tt+|is|hæ}}, {{tt|is|[[hæ]] [[hæ]]}}, {{tt+|is|góðan dag}}, {{tt+|is|góðan daginn}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|halo}}\n* Interlingua: {{tt|ia|hallo}}"
  body "\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|haileo}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|pronto}}\n* Jamaican Creole: {{tt|jam|ello}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|もしもし|tr=moshimoshi}}\n* Kazakh: {{tt|kk|алло}}, {{t|kk|бар ма}}\n* Khmer: {{tt|km|អា"
  body "ឡូ}}, {{t|km|អល្លោ}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|여보세요}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+|kmr|elo}}, {{t+|kmr|helo}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{tt+|ky|алло}}\n* Lao: {{tt|lo|ອາໂຫຼ}}, {{tt|lo|ອາໂຫລ}}\n* Latvian: {{tt|l"
  body "v|hallo}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt+|lt|alio}}, {{tt+|lt|klausau}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|ало}}\n* Malagasy: {{tt+|mg|alô}}\n* Malay: {{tt+|ms|helo}}\n* Maltese: {{tt|mt|ħellow}}\n* Marathi: {{t|mr|हॅलो}}\n"
  body "* Mari:\n*: Eastern Mari: {{t|mhr|алло}}\n* Naga:\n*: Khiamniungan Naga: {{t|kix|hǖhêi}}\n* Nepali: {{tt+|ne|हेलो}}, {{tt+|ne|हलो}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt+|nb|hallo}}\n* Odia: {{tt|or|ହ୍ୟାଲୋ}}"
  body "\n* Persian:\n*: Dari: {{tt|prs|هَلو}}\n*: Iranian Persian: {{tt|fa-ira|اَلو|tr=alo}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|halo}}, {{tt|pl|słucham}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|alô}}, {{tt+|pt|estou}}\n* Romani: {{tt|rom|"
  body "àlo}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|alo}}, {{tt|ro|haló}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|алло́}}, {{qualifier|colloquial}} {{tt+|ru|алё}}, {{tt+|ru|слушать|alt=слу́шаю}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|halò}}\n* Serbo-Croa"
  body "tian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|ха̀ло}}, {{tt|sh|молим}}, {{tt|sh|изволите}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|hàlo}}, {{tt+|sh|molim}}, {{tt+|sh|izvolite}}\n* Sicilian: {{t+|scn|prontu}}, {{t|scn|prontu, cu' è?}}\n* S"
  body "lovak: {{tt|sk|haló}}, {{tt|sk|prosím}}\n* Slovene: {{tt|sl|haló?}}, {{tt+|sl|prosim}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|aló}} {{qualifier|Latin America}}, {{tt+|es|bueno}} {{qualifier|Mexico}}, {{tt+|es|diga}} {{"
  body "qualifier|Spain}}, {{tt+|es|dígame}} {{qualifier|Spain}}, {{tt+|es|hola}} {{qualifier|Argentina|Uruguay}}, {{tt+|es|oigo}} {{qualifier|Cuba}}, {{tt+|es|¿sí?}} {{qualifier|Spain}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|"
  body "hallå}}, {{tt+|sv|hej}}, {{tt+|sv|god dag}} {{qualifier|formal}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|helo|alt=helo?}}, {{tt|tl|magandang araw po|alt=magandang araw po!}}\n* Tajik: {{tt+|tg|алло}}, {{tt+|tg|ҳа}}, {{tt"
  body "|tg|лаббай}}\n* Thai: {{tt|th|สวัสดีครับ}}, {{tt|th|สวัสดีค่ะ}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{tt|th|ฮัลโหล}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Tongan: {{tt|to|mālō e lelei}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|alo}}, {{tt+|tr|efe"
  body "ndim}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt|tk|allo}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|алло́}}, {{tt+|uk|слухати|alt=слу́хаю}}\n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|ہَیلو}}, {{tt|ur|ہیلو}}, {{t|ur|ہَلو}}\n* Uyghur: {{tt|ug|ياخشىمۇسىز}}, {{tt|ug|ئەسسال"
  body "امۇ ئەلەيكۇم}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|allo}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|a-lô}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|helo}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt|zza|elo}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|is anyone there?}}{{multitrans|data=\n*"
  body " Afrikaans: {{tt|af|[[Is]] [[daar]] [[iemand?]]}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|هَل مِن أَحَدٍ هُنَا؟}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{tt|aii|ܐܲܠܘܼ؟ ܚܲܕ݇ ܝܠܹܗ ܬܵܡܵܐ؟}}\n* Armenian: {{tt|hy|աու}}\n* Assa"
  body "mese: {{tt|as|কোনোবা আছেনে?}}, {{tt|as|হেল’}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|kimsə var?}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|гэй}}\n* Bengali: {{tt+|bn|ওহে}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|ехо?}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|hola|alt=ho"
  body "la?}}, {{tt|ca|na maria?}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt|yue|喂|tr=wai3}}\n*: Hokkien: {{tt|nan-hbl|有儂無？|tr=ū lâng bô}}\n*: Mandarin: {{tt|cmn|[[有]][[人]][[嗎]]？|tr=yǒu rén ma?}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|hal"
  body "ó}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|hallo}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|hallo|alt=hallo?}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|hola}}\n* Estonian: {{tt+|et|halloo|alt=halloo?}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|huhuu|alt=huhuu?}}, {{tt|fi|[[haloo]]?"
  body "}}\n* French: {{tt|fr|eh oh|alt=eh oh ?}}, {{tt|fr|oh eh|alt=oh eh ?}}, {{tt+|fr|allô|alt= allô ?}}, {{tt+|fr|ohé|alt=ohé !}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|hallo|alt=hallo?}}, {{tt|de|jemand da?}}\n* Hebrew: {{"
  body "tt|he|שלום? מישהו שם?|tr=shalóm?, mísheu shám?}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|hahó}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt+|is|halló|alt=halló?}}\n* Interlingua: {{tt|ia|hallo|alt=hallo?}}\n* Italian: {{tt|it|[[c'è nessuno]]?"
  body "|lit=there is no one here?}}, {{tt|it|c'è qualcuno|alt=c'è qualcuno?}}\n* Japanese: {{tt|ja|おーい|tr=ōi}} {{qualifier|formal and informal}}, {{tt|ja|すみませーん|tr=sumimasēn}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{tt+|ja|"
  body "ちょっと|tr=chotto}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{qualifier|on the phone}} {{tt+|ja|もしもし|tr=moshimoshi}}\n* Korean: {{tt|ko|계세요?}} {{qualifier|formal}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt+|lt|sveiki}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk"
  body "|ало́}}\n* Malay: {{tt+|ms|helo}}\n* Maltese: {{tt|mt|hawn xi ħadd?}}\n* Nepali: {{t|ne|को छ त्यहाँ}}, {{t|ne|को हो त्यहाँ?}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt+|nb|hallo|alt=hallo?}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{tt|nn"
  body "|hallo|alt=hallo?}}\n* Odia: {{tt+|or|ନମସ୍କାର}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|halo?}}, {{tt|pl|jest tu kto?}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|olá|alt=olá?}}\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|alo|alt=alo?}}, {{tt|ro|haló|alt=haló?}"
  body "}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|ау́}}, {{tt|ru|е́сть кто́-нибудь?}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|ха̀ло}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|hàlo}}\n* Slovak: {{tt|sk|haló}}\n* Slovene: {{tt|sl|haló?}}\n* Spanish:"
  body " {{tt+|es|aló|alt=¿aló?}}, {{tt|es|[[hola|¡Hola!]] [[hay alguien|¿Hay alguien?]]}} {{qualifier|Latin America}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|hallå}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|tao po|alt=tao po?!}}, {{tt+|tl|sino|alt"
  body "=sino po nandyan?}}\n* Tatar: {{t|tt|әй}}, {{t|tt|кем булса да бармы?}}\n* Telugu: {{tt|te|ఎవరైనా ఉంది}}\n* Thai: {{tt|th|มีใครอยู่ไหม?|tr=mii krai yùu mǎi?}}\n* Turkish: {{tt|tr|orda kimse var mı?}},"
  body " {{t|tr|kimse yok mu?}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|аго́в}}\n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|کوئی ہے؟|tr=ko͞i hai?}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|ơi}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|helo?}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt|zza|hımın|m-d}}, {{tt|zza|kam es"
  body "to}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|sarcastic: that was foolish}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Afrikaans: {{t-needed|af}}\n* Arabic: {{t-needed|ar}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{tt|aii|ܐܲܠܘܼ}"
  body "}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|ало}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|喂|tr=wèi}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|hallo|alt=hallo!}}, {{tt+|da|hey|alt=hey!}}\n* Dutch: {{tt|nl|ja, hallo|alt=ja, hallo!}}\n* Estonian: {{"
  body "tt+|et|halloo|alt=halloo!}}, {{tt+|et|tere hommikust|alt=tere hommikust!}}, {{tt|et|tere tali|alt=tere tali!}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|haloo|alt=haloo!}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|ho}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|hall"
  body "o|alt=hallo!}}, {{tt|de|halloho|alt=halloho!}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt|he|הלו|tr=hálo}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt|hu|[[jól]] [[vagy]]?}}, {{tt|hu|[[magad]][[-nál|nál]] [[vagy]]?}}, {{tt|hu|[[ész]][[-nél|nél]] [[vagy"
  body "]]?}}, {{tt|hu|[[ész|esz]][[-ed|ed]][[-nél|nél]] [[vagy]]?}}, {{tt|hu|[[normális]] [[vagy]]?}} {{q|rude}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt+|is|halló|alt=halló!}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|ciao}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|やれ"
  body "やれ|tr=yareyare}} {{qualifier|formal and informal}}, {{tt|ja|やれやれだぜ|tr=yareyare daze}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{tt|ja|[[大丈夫]]？|tr=daijōbu?}} {{qualifier|formal and informal}}, {{tt|ja|大丈夫かよ|tr=daijōbu"
  body " kayo?}} {{qualifier|more informal}}, {{tt|ja|[[マジ]]？|tr=maji?}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{tt|ja|[[マジかよ]]？|tr=maji kayo?}} {{qualifier|more informal}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|[[ало]]оо?}}\n* Norwegian:"
  body "\n*: Bokmål: {{tt+|nb|hallo}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{tt|nn|hallo}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|acorda}}, {{tt+|pt|alô}}\n* Romanian: {{tt|ro|aloo}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|здра́сте}}, {{t|ru|здра́сте Но́вый Го́д}}\n*"
  body " Slovene: {{tt|sl|haló!}}\n* Swedish: {{tt|sv|men hallå}}, {{tt|sv|hallå där}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt+|tl|hoy|alt=hoy!}}, {{tt|tl|huy|alt=huy!}}, {{tt|tl|oy|alt=oy!}}/{{tt+|tl|oi|alt=oi!}}, {{tt|tl|uy|alt=u"
  body "y!}}/{{tt|tl|ui|alt=ui!}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|này!}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|expression of puzzlement}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Afrikaans: {{t-needed|af}}\n* Arabic: {{t-needed|ar}}\n* A"
  body "ramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{tt|aii|ܐܲܠܘܼ}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt+|be|але́}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|моля}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|conill!}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t-needed|cmn}}\n* Danish: {{tt"
  body "+|da|hallo|alt=hallo?}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|hallo|alt=hallo!}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|oho}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|ouah}}\n* Frisian:\n*: West Frisian: {{tt|fy|hallo|alt=hallo!}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|hallo}}"
  body "\n* Hebrew: {{tt|he|הלו|tr=hálo}}\n* Hindi: {{tt|hi|tr=kya}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt+|is|halló}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|本当？|tr=hontō}} {{q|Sure?|formal}}, {{tt|ja|冗談だろ？|tr=jōdan daro}} {{q|You are joking, f"
  body "ormal and informal}}, {{tt+|ja|大丈夫？|tr=daijōbu?}} {{q|Are you all right?|formal and informal}}, {{tt|ja|大丈夫かよ？|tr=daijōbu kayo?}} {{q|Are you all right?|more informal}}, {{tt+|ja|マジ？|tr=maji?}} {{q|Ar"
  body "e you sure?, You're kidding!|informal}}, {{tt|ja|マジかよ|tr=maji kayo?}} {{q|Are you sure?, You're kidding!|more informal}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|hei}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t-needed|nn}}\n* Portugu"
  body "ese: {{tt|pt|o que}}, {{tt+|pt|oi?}}\n* Romanian: {{tt|ro|ia uite}}\n* Slovene: {{tt|sl|hêj!}}\n* Swedish: {{tt|sv|men hallå}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|uy|alt=uy?!}}/{{tt|tl|ui|alt=ui?!}}, {{tt|tl|huy|alt="
  body "huy?!}}, {{tt|tl|oy|alt=oy?!}}/{{tt+|tl|oi|alt=oi?!}}, {{tt+|tl|hoy|alt=hoy?!}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt|vi|ôi trời!}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt|zza|merhebaa}}, {{tt+|zza|way}}\n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-"
  body "top}}\n* Fijian: {{t+check|fj|bula}}\n* Irish: {{t-check|ga|haló}}\n* Nahuatl: {{t+check|nah|niltze}}\n* Nepali: {{t+check|ne|नमस्कार}}\n* Tatar: {{t-check|tt|[[isänme]](sez)!}}, {{t-check|tt|[[sälâm]"
  body "]!}} (1), {{t-check|tt|allo}}, {{t-check|tt|hallow}} (2)\n* Urdu: {{t+check|ur|آداب|tr=ādāb}}, {{t-check|ur|السلام علیکم|tr=āssālam ‘alaykum}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|chào}} ({{t+|vi|ông}}, {{t+|vi|bà}"
  body "}, {{t+|vi|cô}}, {{t+|vi|anh}}, {{t+|vi|chị}}, {{t+|vi|em}}, {{t|vi|quí vị}}) {{attention|vi|please add qualifier for each one on gender and relative social status of person addressed}}\n* Woiwurrung:"
  body " {{t-check|wyi|gudjinna}}, {{t-check|wyi|wawa}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====See also====\n* [[:Category:English greetings]]\n* {{pedia}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|s|es}}\n\n# \""[[hello#Interjection|Hello]"
  body "]!\"" or an equivalent greeting.\n#: {{ux|en|They gave each other a quick '''hello''' when they met, and went back on their merry ways.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=April 29, 2007|author=Stephanie Ros"
  body "enbloom|title=A Beautiful Day in the Neighborhood|work=New York Times|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/04/29/fashion/29condo.html\n|passage=In many new buildings, though, neighbors are venturing beyond"
  body " tight-lipped '''hellos''' at the mailbox.}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|en|greeting}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|say hello to my little friend}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb|+,~es}}\n\n# {{lb|en|t"
  body "ransitive}} To [[greet]] with \""hello\"".\n#* {{quote-journal|en|journal=Records and Briefs in Cases Decided by the Supreme Court of Minnesota|year=1891|page=227|passage=She is there guarding and looki"
  body "ng after the candy and the children generally, and she '''helloes''' and renders an exclamation that Maidie is crossing the street.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|journal=Ohio State Engineer|year=1927|page="
  body "18|passage=He '''helloes''' to my daughter:{{...}}}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=w:Mark Dolan|title=Do You Mind if I Put My Hand on it?: Journeys into the Worlds of the Weird|publisher=[[w:HarperCollin"
  body "s|HarperCollins''Publishers'']]|year=2012|isbn=9780007481873|passage=‘Hello Minka! Great to meet you!’ Minka seems nonplussed at what I thought was an uncontroversial opening remark. There’s an awkwar"
  body "d pause. She then '''helloes''' me back. But that’s all I get.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2013|author=Ivan Doig|title=English Creek|page=139|passage=I had to traipse around somewhat, '''helloing''' pe"
  body "ople and being '''helloed''', before I spotted my mother and my father, sharing shade and a spread blanket with Pete and Marie Reese and Toussaint Rennie near the back of the park.}}\n\n===Anagrams==="
  body "\n* {{anagrams|en|a=ehllo|Holle}}\n\n{{cln|en|calculator words|greetings}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|fr|en|hello}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|hèllo|[h]èllo}}\n* {{audio|fr|"
  body "LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-hello.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{head|fr|interjection}}\n\n# {{lb|fr|anglicism}} {{l|en|hello}}, [[hi]]\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n"
  body "\n{{cln|fr|greetings}}\n\n==Fula==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{rfe|ff}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{ff-noun|ngo|hellooji|ɗi}}\n\n# a [[page]]\n# one side of a [[wall]], a wall\n# a [[slap]] in the face\n\n===Referenc"
  body "es===\n* {{R:Bah 2014}}""}}"

