  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=hi&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "{""parse"":{""title"":""hi"",""pageid"":4804,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""{{also|Appendix:Variations of \""hi\""}}\n{{minitoc}}\n==Translingual==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{clip|mul|en:'''Hi'''ndi}}, from {{der|mul|hi"
  body "|हिन्दी|tr='''hi'''ndī}}, from {{der|mul|fa-cls|هِنْدِی|tr='''hi'''ndī}}.\n\n===Symbol===\n{{mul-symbol}}\n\n# {{ISO 639|1}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{langcat}}\n\n==English==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n[[Ame"
  body "rican English]]. First recorded reference is to speech of a Kansas Indian (1862); originally to attract attention, probably a variant of {{inh|en|enm|hey}}, {{m|enm|hy}} ([[circa]] 1475). Also an excl"
  body "amation to call attention. See {{m|en|hey}}.{{rfref|en}}\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alter|en|heigh}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|en|/haɪ/}}, {{rhymes|en|aɪ|s=1}}\n** {{homophones|en|Hi|hi"
  body "e|high}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-hi.ogg|a=US}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-hi.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{IPA|en|/haːj/|a=Indic}}\n\n====Interjection====\n{{en-intj}}\n\n# {{n-g|A [[friendly]], [[informal]], [[casual]] [[g"
  body "reeting]] said upon someone's [[arrival]].}}\n#: {{syn|en|hello|greetings|howdy}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''Hi''', how are you?}}\n#: {{ux|en|I just dropped by to say “'''hi'''”.}}\n#* '''2016''', [https://web.a"
  body "rchive.org/web/20170925022505/https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/lets-learn-english-lesson-4/3168920.html VOA Learning English] (public domain)\n#*: Anna: Pete, hi! Hi, we are here! &mdash; Pete: H"
  body "i, Anna! Hi, Marsha!  &mdash; Anna: Hi!  &mdash; Pete: How are you two?  &mdash; Marsha: I am great!\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1862|author=Miriam Davis Colt|title=Went to Kansas|url=http://www.kancoll."
  body "org/books/colt/|page=143|publisher=L. Ingalls & Company|isbn=9780608429793|pageurl=https://www.google.com/books/edition/Went_to_Kansas/OVQDAAAAYAAJ?hl=en&gbpv=1&dq=%22hi%22+kansas&pg=PA143&printsec=fr"
  body "ontcover|text=When out on the prairie, up galloped an Indian on his pony with his saluting \""'''hi'''!\""}}\n# {{n-g|An [[exclamation]] to call attention.}}\n#* {{RQ:Lincoln Pratt's Patients|chapter=7|"
  body "passage=I made a speaking trumpet of my hands and commenced to whoop “Ahoy!” and “Hello!” at the top of my lungs. {{...}} The Colonel woke up, and, after asking what in brimstone was the matter, opene"
  body "d his mouth and roared “'''Hi!'''” and “Hello!” like the bull of Bashan.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1954|author=J. R. R. Tolkien|title=The Two Towers|passage='Come back now!' shouted Sam. ''''Hi'''! C"
  body "ome back!' But Gollum had vanished.}}\n# {{lb|en|dated outside of Ireland}} {{n-g|Expressing [[wonder]] or [[derision]].}}\n#: {{ux|en|How did he do that, '''hi'''?}}\n#: {{ux|en|That’s mad, '''hi'''!"
  body "}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col2|en|hi there|hi-bye friend|bonjour/hi|rehi}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n{{top4}}\n* {{desc|tpi|hai}}\n* {{desc|zh|嗨|hi|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|de|hi|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|hi|"
  body "हेलो|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|is|hæ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ms|hai|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ml|ഹായ്|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|vi|hai|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|friendly, informal greeting}}\n{{mul"
  body "titrans|data=\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|haai}}\n* Aleut: {{tt|ale|aang}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{tt|alt|эзен}}\n* Alutiiq: {{t|ems|cama’i}}\n* Ambonese Malay: {{tt|abs|oe}}\n* American Sign Langu"
  body "age: {{tt|ase|B@Sfhead-PalmForward B@FromSfhead-PalmForward}}\n* Amharic: {{tt|am|ሰላም}}\n* Arabic: {{tt+|ar|مَرْحَبًا}}, {{tt+|ar|سَلَام}}, {{tt+|ar|أَهْلًا}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|أهلاً}}\n*:"
  body " Gulf Arabic: {{t|afb|هلا|tr=hala}}, {{t|afb|قوة|tr=guwa}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{tt|acw|هلا|tr=hala}}, {{tt|acw|مَرْحَبَا|tr=marḥaba}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{tt|ary|السلام|tr=s-salām}}\n* Armenian: {{t"
  body "t+|hy|բարև}}\n* Asturian: {{t+|ast|ei}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|salam}}\n* Bashkir: {{tt|ba|сәләм}}\n* Basque: {{tt+|eu|kaixo}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|прыве́т}}, {{tt|be|здаро́ў}}\n* Bengali: {{tt+|b"
  body "n|সালাম|tr=salam}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|здра́сти}}, {{tt+|bg|здраве́й}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|မင်္ဂလာပါ}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|hola}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt|yue|你好|tr=nei5 hou2}}\n*: Dungan:"
  body " {{tt|dng|сэляму}}\n*: Eastern Min: {{tt|cdo|汝好}}\n*: Hakka: {{tt|hak|你好|tr=ngì-hó}}\n*: Hokkien: {{tt|nan-hbl|你好|tr=lí hó}}\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|你好|tr=nǐ hǎo}} {{qualifier|the most common}}, {{tt+"
  body "|cmn|嗨|tr=hāi}} {{tt+|cmn|哈囉|tr=hāluō}} {{qualifier|slang}}\n*: Wu: {{tt|wuu|儂好}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|ahoj}}, {{tt+|cs|čau}}, {{tt+|cs|čus}}, {{tt+|cs|nazdar}}, {{tt+|cs|zdar}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|hall"
  body "o}}, {{tt+|da|hej|alt=hej!}}, {{tt+|da|dav}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|hallo}}, {{tt+|nl|hoi}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt+|eo|saluton}}, {{tt+|eo|sal}}\n* Estonian: {{tt+|et|hei}}, {{tt+|et|tere}}, {{tt|et|tervist}}"
  body "\n* Faroese: {{tt|fo|hey}}, {{tt|fo|halló}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|hei}}, {{tt+|fi|moi}}, {{tt+|fi|terve}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|salut}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|ola}}\n* Georgian: {{tt+|ka|გამარჯობა}}\n* Ge"
  body "rman: {{tt+|de|hallo}}, {{tt|de|'n Tag}}\n*: Alemannic German: {{t|gsw|sali}}, {{t|gsw|hoi}}, {{t|gsw|grüezi}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|el|γεια}}\n* Hebrew: {{tt+|he|שָׁלוֹם|tr=shalóm}}, {{tt+|he|היי|tr=haj}}\"
  body "n* Hindi: {{tt+|hi|नमस्ते}}, {{tt+|hi|सलाम}} {{qualifier|used by Muslims}}, {{tt+|hi|हाइ}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|szia}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt+|is|halló}}, {{tt+|is|hæ}}\n* Indonesian: {{tt+|id|hai}}, {{"
  body "tt+|id|salam}}\n* Interlingua: {{tt+|ia|salute}}, {{tt|ia|hallo}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|haigh}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|ciao}}\n* Japanese: {{tt+|ja|こんにちは|tr=konnichi wa}}, {{tt+|ja|やあ|tr=yā}}, {{tt+|ja|どうも|t"
  body "r=dōmo}}, {{tt+|ja|よう|tr=yō}}\n* Kazakh: {{tt|kk|сәлем}}, {{tt|kk|салам}}\n* Khmer: {{tt|km|សួស្តី}}\n* Korean: {{tt+|ko|안녕(安寧)}}\n* Krio: {{tt|kri|kusheh}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{tt+|kmr"
  body "|merheba}}, {{tt+|kmr|silav}}, {{tt+|kmr|selam}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{tt+|ky|салам}}\n* Lao: {{tt+|lo|ສະບາຍດີ}}, {{tt|lo|ເຮີຍ}}\n* Latin: {{tt+|la|salve}}, {{tt+|la|ave}}\n* Latvian: {{qualifier|gender depend"
  body "ing on the listener(s)}} {{tt+|lv|sveiks|m}}, {{tt|lv|sveika|f}}, {{tt|lv|sveiki|m-p}}, {{tt|lv|sveikas|f-p}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt+|lt|labas}}, {{tt+|lt|sveikas}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|здраво}}\n* Mal"
  body "ay: {{tt+|ms|hai}}, {{tt+|ms|salam}}\n* Maltese: {{tt|mt|ejj}}\n* Mansi:\n*: Eastern Mansi: {{t|mns-eas|пяся}}\n*: Northern Mansi: {{t|mns-nor|паща}}, {{t|mns-nor|пася}}\n*: Southern Mansi: {{t|mns-no"
  body "r|tr=piśėn}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt+|mn|сайн уу?}} {{q|informal}}, {{tt+|mn|сайн байна уу?}}\n* Nepali: {{tt+|ne|हाइ}} {{tt+|ne|नमस्कार}}, {{tt+|ne|नमस्ते}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{tt+|n"
  body "b|hei}}, {{tt|nb|heisan}}\n* Occitan: {{tt+|oc|adieu}}\n* Ojibwe: {{tt|oj|boozhoo}}\n* Ossetian: {{tt|os|салам}}, {{tt|os|арфӕ}}\n* Pashto: {{tt+|ps|سلام|tr=salām}}\n* Persian:\n*: Iranian Persian: {{"
  body "tt|fa-ira|سَلام}}, {{tt|fa-ira|دُرود}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|cześć}}, {{tt+|pl|hej}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|olá}}, {{tt+|pt|oi}}, {{tt+|pt|alô}}, {{tt+|pt|e aí|alt=e ai?}}\n* Punjabi: (''sat sri akal''"
  body ", formal), (''kiddhan'', informal)\n* Romanian: {{tt+|ro|bună}}, {{tt+|ro|salut}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|приве́т}}, {{tt+|ru|здоро́во}}, {{tt+|ru|здра́сте}}\n* Sami:\n*: Inari Sami: {{tt|smn|tiervâ}}\n*"
  body ": Northern Sami: {{tt|se|dearvva}}, {{tt|se|bures}}\n*: Skolt Sami: {{tt|sms|tiõrv}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt|gd|hòigh}}, {{t|gd|shin thu}} {{qualifier|informal and singular}}, {{t|gd|shin sibh}} {{qu"
  body "alifier|plural or formal}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|ћа̑о}}, {{tt|sh|здра̏во}}, {{tt|sh|ме̏рха̄ба}}, {{tt|sh|ха̀ло}}, {{tt|sh|бок}}\n*: Latin: {{tt|sh|ćȃo}}, {{tt+|sh|zdrȁvo}}, {{tt|sh|"
  body "mȅrhāba}}, {{tt+|sh|hàlo}}, {{tt+|sh|bok}}\n* Sicilian: {{tt|scn|sabbinirìca}}\n* Slovak: {{tt+|sk|ahoj}}, {{tt|sk|čau}}, {{tt|sk|nazdar}}\n* Slovene: {{tt|sl|žívjo}}, {{tt|sl|zdrávo}}\n* Spanish: {{t"
  body "t+|es|hola}}\n* Sranan Tongo: {{tt|srn|fa}}, {{tt|srn|ofa}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|jambo}}, {{tt|sw|salaam}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|hallå}}, {{tt+|sv|hej|alt=hej!}}, {{tt+|sv|hejsan}}, {{tt+|sv|tja}}, {{t"
  body "t+|sv|tjena}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt|tl|helo}}, {{tt+|tl|hoy}}\n* Tajik: {{tt|tg|салом}}\n* Tamil: {{tt+|ta|வணக்கம்}}\n* Tatar: {{tt+|tt|сәлам}}\n* Thai: {{tt|th|หวัดดี}}, {{tt+|th|สวัสดี}}\n* Tigrinya: {{t"
  body "t|ti|ሰላም}}\n* Tok Pisin: {{tt|tpi|gude}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|merhaba}}, {{tt+|tr|selam}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt|tk|salam}}\n* Tz'utujil: {{tt|tzj|coli}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|приві́т}}, {{tt|uk|се́рвус}}\"
  body "n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|سَلام}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{tt|ur|اَلسَّلامُ عَلَیکُم|tr=as-salāmu 'alaikum}} {{qualifier|slightly formal}}, {{tt|ur|سَلام عَلَیکُم}} {{qualifier|common}}, {{tt+|ur|آداب}} {{qua"
  body "lifier|dated or formal}}\n* Uyghur: {{tt|ug|سالام}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|salom}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|chào}} (depending on the relationship between speaker and person addressed, one of the following "
  body "terms may be appended: {{tt+|vi|ông}}, {{tt+|vi|bà}}, {{tt+|vi|cô}}, {{tt+|vi|anh}}, {{tt+|vi|chị}}, {{tt+|vi|em}}, {{tt|vi|quí vị}})\n* Volapük: {{t-check|vo|glidis|alt=glidis!}} {{attention|vo|2=was"
  body " \""[[glidis]]!\"" - assumed inflected form or vocalised spelling; please verify if linking is acceptable. see [[User:So9q/Improved-xte.js/documentation#Translation_fixing]]}}\n* Walloon: {{tt+|wa|a}}, "
  body "{{tt+|wa|bondjoû}}\n* Welsh: {{tt|cy|siwmae}}\n* Xârâgurè: {{t|axx|vâsgatzo}}\n* Zhuang: {{t-needed|za}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# The word \"""
  body "hi\"" used as a greeting.\n#: {{syn|en|greeting|hello}}\n#: {{ux|en|I didn't even get a '''hi'''.}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{m|en|high}}.\n\n====Adjective====\n{{head|en|adjective}}\n\n# {{informal"
  body " spelling of|en|high|addl=often in hyphenated terms}}.\n#: {{ux|en|Get '''hi-'''quality videos here!}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col4|en|hi-score|hi-def|hi-fi|hi-five|hi-hat|hi-lo|Hi-NRG|hi-res|hi"
  body "-rise|hi-tech|hi-top|hi-vis|hi-way}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n* {{l|en|lo}}\n* {{l|en|mid}}\n\n===See also===\n{{col2|en|title=etymologically unrelated terms containing the word \""hi\""|hi-rail|hi-w"
  body "a itck|hi-ya|qui-hi|hi-spy-hi}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=hi|IH}}\n\n{{cln|en|2-letter words|greetings|calculator words}}\n\n==Albanian==\n\n===Etymology===\nTosk form of [[Gheg]] {{m|sq|hî"
  body "}} (pl. ''hin''), from {{inh|sq|sqj-pro|*skina}}, from {{m|sq|*skines}}, from {{inh|sq|ine-pro|*ḱenHis}} (compare {{cog|la|cinis||dust; cinder}}, {{cog|grc|κόνις||ashes; dust}}).\n\n===Noun===\n{{sq-n"
  body "oun|m||hiri}}\n\n# [[ash]], [[ashes]]\n# [[dust]] of corpses\n# {{lb|sq|figurative}} memory of the dead\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|sq|hirët}}\n* {{l|sq|hirtë}}\n* {{l|sq|hith}}\n\n===Further read"
  body "ing===\n* {{R:sq:FMGSH:2026}}\n\n==Antigua and Barbuda Creole English==\n\n===Pronoun===\n{{head|aig|pronoun}}\n\n# [[he]]\n# [[his]]\n\n==Basque==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|eu|LL-Q8752 (eus)-"
  body "Aioramu-hi.wav}}\n{{eu-pr}}\n\n===Pronoun===\n{{head|eu|pronoun|cat2=personal pronouns|emphatic forms|[[heu]], [[hihaur]], [[herori]]}}\n\n# {{lb|eu|informal|familiar}} {{non-gloss|Second-person singu"
  body "lar personal pronoun}}; [[you]]\n\n====Usage notes====\n* This pronoun is very informal, and is only used between close friends or family members. In all other situations, {{m|eu|zu}} is used.\n* When"
  body " addressing someone using this pronoun, all verb forms (including those not governed by ''hi'') must be in {{w|allocutive agreement}}. For example:\n*: {{uxi|eu|Mahaia handia '''da'''.|The table '''is"
  body "''' big.}}\n*: {{uxi|eu|Mahaia handia '''duk'''.|The table '''is''' big. (informal, to a male)}}\n*: {{uxi|eu|Mahaia handia '''dun'''.|The table '''is''' big. (informal, to a female)}}\n\n====Declensi"
  body "on====\n{{eu-decl-pron}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|eu|hiketa|t=use of ''hi''}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|eu|heu}}\n\n===See also===\n{{eu-personal pronouns}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{"
  body "R:eu:EH}}\n* {{R:eu:OEH}}\n\n==Bavarian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|bar|/hiː/}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|bar|gmh|hin}}, {{m|gmh|hine}}, from {{inh|bar|goh|hina}}. Compare {{cog|de|hin}},"
  body " {{cog|nl|heen}} and {{cog|en|hence}}.\n\n====Adverb====\n{{bar-adverb}}\n\n# {{senseid|bar|away}}{{ng|Used to denote direction away from the speaker.}}\n#: {{uxi|bar|Wo gehst'n '''hi'''?|Where are yo"
  body "u going?}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|bar|dåhi}}\n* {{l|bar|duathi}}\n\n=====See also=====\n{{bar-local adverbs}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nClipping of {{der|bar|gmh|hinüber}}.\n\n====Adjective===="
  body "\n{{head|bar|adj|predicative}}\n\n# [[out of order]], [[broken]]\n#: {{uxi|bar|Des Auto is '''hi'''.|The car is '''broken'''.}}\n# [[exhausted]], [[depleted]]\n#: {{uxi|bar|Nåchn Spuat gestern woar i "
  body "afoch nur '''hi'''.|I was just '''exhausted''' after yesterday's sport.}}\n# {{lb|bar|derogatory}} [[dead]], [[deceased]]\n#: {{uxi|bar|Auffigstiegn, owigfoin, '''hi''' gwen.|Ascended, fell off, '''de"
  body "ad'''.}}\n# {{lb|bar|figuratively|derogatory|chiefly|East Central|Vienna}} [[stupid]]\n#: {{syn|bar|ågrennt|deppert|waach}}\n#: {{uxi|bar|Bist '''hi''' in der Marün?|Are you stupid?}}\n\n=====Synonyms"
  body "=====\n* {{l|bar|hinich|hinig}}\n\n==Breton==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|br|cel-pro|*sī}}. Cognate to {{cog|cy|hi}}.\n\n===Pronoun===\n{{head|br|pronouns|cat2=personal pronouns}}\n\n# [[she]]\n\n="
  body "==See also===\n{{br-personal pronouns}}\n\n==Catalan==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{inh+|ca|roa-oca|y}}, {{m|roa-oca|i}}, {{m|roa-oca|hic}}, from {{inh|ca|la|hīc||here}} and {{m|la|ibī||there}}. Compare {{co"
  body "g|fr|y}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{ca-IPA}}\n* {{homophones|ca|i}}\n* {{rhymes|ca|i}}\n\n===Pronoun===\n{{ca-ppron|type=encl+procl}}\n\n# ''represents a place associated with the action described b"
  body "y the verb, unless the place would be introduced by the preposition [[de#Catalan|de]]''\n# [[there]] (in constructions such as \""[[there is]]\"", \""[[there are]]\"", etc.: ''see'' {{l|ca|haver-hi}})\n# "
  body "''replaces an adverb (or adverbial phrase) describing the manner, instrument or association of an action''\n# ''replaces a phrase introduced by any preposition except [[de#Catalan|de]] (most commonly "
  body "[[a/languages A to L#Catalan|a]] or [[en#Catalan|en]])''\n# ''replaces an indefinite noun or an adjective which is the predicate of a verb ''other'' than {{l|ca|ésser}}, {{l|ca|esdevenir}}, [[estar#Ca"
  body "talan|estar]] or [[semblar#Catalan|semblar]]''\n# {{lb|ca|Central Catalan}} ''in combination with other object pronouns, the third-person singular indirect object pronoun'' (\""to him\"", \""to her\"", \"""
  body "to it\"")\n\n====Usage notes====\n* When more than one object pronoun is associated with a given verb, '''hi''' is always the last in the group.\n* '''Hi''' and [[ho#Catalan|ho]] cannot be used togethe"
  body "r with the same verb, nor can two '''hi'''s be used together.\n* It is sometimes stated that '''hi''' is ''never'' used to replace a complement beginning with [[de#Catalan|de]]. This is not completely"
  body " accurate, as '''hi''' can replace ''adverbial'' phrases such as [[de pressa]], [[de sobte]], etc.\n\n====Declension====\n{{ca-personal pronouns}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{sense|Proclitic contrac"
  body "tions}} {{l|ca|l'hi}}, {{l|ca|m'hi}}, {{l|ca|n'hi}}, {{l|ca|s'hi}}, {{l|ca|t'hi}}\n* {{sense|Enclitic contractions}} {{l|ca|-ens-hi}}, {{l|ca|-l'hi}}, {{l|ca|-la-hi}}, {{l|ca|-les-hi}}, {{l|ca|-los-hi"
  body "}}, {{l|ca|'ls-hi}}, {{l|ca|-m'hi}}, {{l|ca|-n'hi}}, {{l|ca|'ns-hi}}, {{l|ca|-s'hi}}, {{l|ca|-t'hi}}, {{l|ca|-us-hi}}, {{l|ca|-vos-hi}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|ca|en}} ''pron''\n* {{l|ca|ho}} ''pron'"
  body "'\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:ca:IEC2}}\n\n==Chinese==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{zh-pron\n|c=haai1\n|cat=intj,v\n}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{bor|yue|en|hi}}. {{doublet|zh|嗨}}.\n\n====Interject"
  body "ion====\n{{head|zh|interjection}}\n\n# {{lb|zh|Hong Kong Cantonese}} [[#English|hi]] {{gl|interjection}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{bor|yue|en|hi}}, see {{m|zh|hi auntie}} for more.\n\n====Verb====\"
  body "n{{head|zh|verb}}\n\n# {{lb|zh|Hong Kong Cantonese|euphemistic|originally|Internet slang|neologism}} {{alt form|yue|屌}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n* {{l|zh|hi auntie}}\n\n=====See also=====\n* {{l|zh"
  body "|hihi}}\n* {{zh-l|向左走向右走}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\nIrregular romanisation of {{m|yue|揩}}.\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|zh|verb}}\n\n# {{lb|zh|Hong Kong Cantonese}} {{alt form|yue|揩}}\n\n{{cln|zh|greetings}}\"
  body "n\n==Cornish==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|kw|cel-bry-pro|*hi}}, from {{inh|kw|cel-pro|*sī}}. Cognate with {{cog|br,cy|hi}}, and {{cog|ga|sí}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alt|kw|hei||RLC}}"
  body "\n\n====Pronoun====\n{{head|kw|pronoun|g=f}}\n\n# [[she]] (third-person feminine singular personal pronoun).\n#: {{ux|kw|'''Hi''' a welas.|She saw.}}\n# [[her]] (third-person feminine singular encliti"
  body "c pronoun, used to reinforce previous pronoun).\n#: {{ux|kw|hy lyver '''hi'''|her book}}\n#: {{ux|kw|Ple eth '''hi'''?|Where did she go?}}\n\n====See also====\n{{kw-personal pronouns}}\n\n===Etymology"
  body " 2===\n{{non-lemma}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|kw|mutated noun}}\n\n# {{aspirate mutation of|kw|ki}}\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{rhymes|da|i}}\n* {{rhymes|da|iː}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFro"
  body "m {{der|da|no|hi}}, from {{der|da|non|hið}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{da-noun|et|er}}\n\n# winter [[quarters]], winter [[lair]] (for hibernation); [[hibernation]] {{q|used literally or figuratively}}\n#: at"
  body " gå i '''hi'''\n#:: to enter '''hibernation'''\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{da-noun-infl|et|er}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{l|da|vinterhi}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nOnomatopoeia for laughter or giggling.\n"
  body "\n====Interjection====\n{{head|da|intj}}\n\n# {{lb|da|onomatopoeia}} {{non-gloss|Signifies giggling.}}\n\n=====See also=====\n* {{l|da|ha}}\n\n==Fasu==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|faa|noun|head=hị}}\n\n# {{"
  body "lb|faa|Namumi}} {{synonym of|faa|he}}\n\n===References===\n* Karl J. Franklin, ''[https://web.archive.org/web/20160305070551/http://www-01.sil.org/pacific/png/pubs/10745/Comp_Wordlist_Gulfdistrict.pdf"
  body " Comparative Wordlist 1 of the Gulf District and adjacent areas]'' (1975), page 67\n\n==German==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|de|en|hi}}, from 1990s digitalization.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|de|/ˈ"
  body "haɪ̯/}}\n* {{audio|de|De-hi.ogg|a=<<Germany>> (<<Berlin>>)}}\n* {{rhymes|de|aɪ̯}}\n* {{homophones|de|hei|high}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{head|de|interjection}}\n\n# {{tlb|de|very|_|informal}} {{l|en|h"
  body "i}}\n#: {{syn|de|moin}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:de:DWDS|hi}}\n\n{{cln|de|greetings}}\n\n==Japanese==\n\n===Romanization===\n{{ja-romaji}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|ja|syllable|ひ|ヒ|hi}}\n\n==Kankanaey==\"
  body "n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{kne-pr}}\n\n===Article===\n{{kne-head|article}}\n\n# {{dialectal form of|kne|si}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n{{dial syn|kne|si}}\n\n==Latin==\n\n===Pronoun===\n{{head|la|pronoun fo"
  body "rm|head=hī}}\n\n# {{inflection of|la|hic||nom|m|p}}\n\n==Maltese==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|mt|ar|هِيَ}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|mt|/iː/}}\n* {{rhymes|mt|iː|s=1}}\n\n===Pronoun===\n{{mt"
  body "-pronoun}}\n\n# {{alternative form of|mt|hija}}\n\n====Inflection====\n{{mt-hija}}\n\n==Middle Dutch==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|dum|gmw-pro|gem-pro|inh=2}}\nFrom {{inh|dum|odt|hīe}}.\n\n===Pronunc"
  body "iation===\n* {{IPA|dum|/hiː/}}\n\n===Pronoun===\n{{head|dum|pronoun}}\n\n# [[he]]\n\n====Inflection====\n{{dum-personal pronouns}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|nl|hij|ie}}\n* {{desc|li|hae}}\n\n=="
  body "=Further reading===\n* {{R:VMNW|ID34}}\n* {{R:MNW|17185|I}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Pronoun====\n{{head|enm|pronoun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|I|t=I|id=I}}\n\n===Etymol"
  body "ogy 2===\n\n====Pronoun====\n{{head|enm|pronoun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|he|t=he|id=he}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\n\n====Pronoun====\n{{head|enm|pronoun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|heo|t=she|"
  body "id=she}}\n\n===Etymology 4===\n\n====Pronoun====\n{{head|enm|pronoun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|he|t=they|id=they}}\n\n==Middle Low German==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* Possibly: {{IPA|gml|/hiː/}}"
  body "\n* Certainly: '''[[Wiktionary:About_Middle_Low_German#Stem_vowels|Stem vowel]]: ê⁴'''\n** {{IPA|gml|/hiɛ/|/hiə/}}\n\n===Pronoun===\n{{head|gml|pronoun|head=hî}}\n\n# {{alternative form of|gml|hê}}\n\"
  body "n==Mizo==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|lus|tbq-kuk-pro|*hii}}.\n\n===Determiner===\n{{head|lus|determiner|pronominal|hei|or|he|oblique|hian}}\n\n# [[this]], [[these]] (near the speaker)\n\n====See a"
  body "lso====\n{{lus-demonstratives}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:lus:Lorrain}}\n\n==Naga Pidgin==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|nag|hi|ही}}.\n\n===Particle===\n{{head|nag|particle}}\n\n# {{n-g|an [[em"
  body "phatic]] [[particle]]}}\n\n==Namuyi==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{nmy-IPA}}\n* {{hyph|nmy|hi}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|nmy|noun}}\n\n# [[month]]\n\n===References===\n* {{R:nmy:Li:2017|page=472}}\n\n==No"
  body "rth Frisian==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{l|frr|he}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|frr|ofs|hī}}, from {{inh|frr|gmw-pro|*hiʀ}}, from {{inh|frr|gem-pro|*hiz}}, from {{inh|frr|ine-pro|*ḱe}}.\n\n==="
  body "Pronoun===\n{{head|frr|pronoun}}\n\n# [[he]]\n#: {{uxi|frr|'''Hi''' wal sin frinjer üüb Feer beschük.|'''He''' wants to visit his relatives on Föhr.}}\n\n==Norwegian Nynorsk==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n"
  body "* {{IPA|nn|/hiː/}} {{nn-pronu-note}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{der|nn|non|hið}} and {{m|non|híði}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{nn-noun-n1}}\n\n# [[lair]] {{q|of an animal}}, [[sett]] {{q|badgers}}\n#: {{us"
  body "ex|nn|Bjørnane har gått i '''hi''' for vinteren.|The bears have entered their '''lairs''' for the winter.}}\n#: {{ux|nn|Bjørnen søv no, bjørnen søv no i sitt lune '''hi'''|The bear is sleeping now, th"
  body "e bear is sleeping now in his cozy '''lair''' (''a children song'')}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Determiner====\n{{head|nn|determiner form|g=f|masculine|hin|neuter|hitt|plural|hine}}\n\n# {{feminine "
  body "singular of|nn|hin}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\n\n====Interjection====\n{{head|nn|interjection}}\n\n# [[hee]]; expression of [[snickering]]\n\n===References===\n* {{R:nn:OB}}\n\n==Old English==\n\n===Pronu"
  body "nciation===\n* {{ang-IPA|hī}}\n* {{rhymes|ang|iː|s=1}}\n\n===Pronoun===\n{{head|ang|pronoun|head=hī}}\n\n# {{alternative form of|ang|hīe||they}}\n\n==Old Frisian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|ofs|ine"
  body "-pro|inh=1}}\nFrom {{inh|ofs|gmw-pro|*hiʀ}}, from {{inh|ofs|gem-pro|[[*hiz]]}}. Cognates include {{cog|ang|hē}} and {{cog|odt|hie}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ofs|/ˈhiː/}}\n\n===Pronoun===\n{{he"
  body "ad|ofs|pronoun|head=hī|g=m|accusative|hine|genitive|sīn|dative|him}}\n\n# {{l|en|he}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{ofs-personal pronouns}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|frr|-}}\n*: Most dialects: {{l|f"
  body "rr|hi}}, {{l|frr|he}}\n*: Halligen: {{l|frr|hii}}\n* {{desc|stq|hie}}\n* {{desc|fy|hy}}\n\n====References====\n* {{R:ofs:Bremmer:2009}}\n\n==Old Irish==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Preposition====\n{{"
  body "head|sga|prepositions}}\n\n# {{alt sp|sga|i}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Particle====\n{{head|sga|particle}}\n\n# {{alt sp|sga|í}}\n\n==Pali==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n{{pi-alt}}\n\n===Conjunction"
  body "===\n{{head|pi|conjunction}}\n\n# [[for]], [[because]]\n\n===Adverb===\n{{head|pi|adverb}}\n\n# [[indeed]], [[certainly]]\n\n====References====\n* {{R:pi:Childers}}\n* {{R:pi:PTS}}\n\n==Pirahã==\n\n=="
  body "=Etymology===\nPossibly {{bor+|myp|yrl|i|nocap=1}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|myp|/hɪ̃̀/}}\n\n===Pronoun===\n{{head|myp|pronoun}}\n\n# [[he]], [[she]] (third-person subject pronoun)\n# [[him]], "
  body "[[her]] (third-person object pronoun)\n\n==Sumerian==\n\n===Romanization===\n{{sux-rom}}\n\n# {{romanization of|sux|𒄭|tr=ḫi}}\n\n==Vietnamese==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{vi-IPA}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{vi-v"
  body "erb}}\n\n# to [[bare]] one's [[teeth]]\n#: {{ux|vi|Hi răng ra coi nào.|Come on, show me your teeth.}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|vi|nhe}}\n\n==Waray-Waray==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{inh+|war|map-pro|*si}"
  body "}. Compare {{cog|bcl|si}}, {{cog|ceb|si}}, {{cog|gor|ti}}, {{cog|hil|si}}, {{cog|ilo|si}}, {{cog|pam|i}}, {{cog|pag|si}}, {{cog|tsg|hi}}, and {{cog|war|si}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{war-IPA}}\n\n==="
  body "Article===\n{{war-head|article}}\n\n# {{n-g|direct marker placed before names or terms of address of people}}\n\n==Welsh==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|cy|/hiː/}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|c"
  body "y|cel-pro|*sī}} (compare {{cog|sga|sí}}).\n\n====Pronoun====\n{{head|cy|pronoun|cat2=personal pronouns}}\n\n# [[she]], [[her]]\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|cy|mutated noun}}\n\n# {{h-p"
  body "rothesis of|cy|i}}\n\n====Mutation====\n{{cy-mut|i}}\n\n==Yilan Creole==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|ycr|ja|-}} {{ja-r|火|ひ|t=fire}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ycr|/hi/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head"
  body "|ycr|noun}}\n\n# {{lb|ycr|Aohua}} [[fire]]\n\n===References===\n* {{R:ycr:Lin 2022}}\n\n{{C|ycr|Fire}}\n\n==Yola==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|yol|h'}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|yol|enm"
  body "|he|hi|t=they, them}}, from {{inh|yol|ang|hīe}}, {{m|ang|hī}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|yol|/hiː/|/h/}}\n* {{homophones|yol|hea|hie}}\n\n===Pronoun===\n{{head|yol|pronoun}}\n\n# [[they]]\n#* {{"
  body "quote-book|yol|year=1867|page=86<ref name=Poole>{{R:Poole 1867}}</ref>\n|chapter=A YOLA ZONG|number=5|title=SONGS, ETC. IN THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|passage=Mot w'all aar boust, '''hi''' soon was"
  body " ee-teight|translation=But with all their bravado '''they''' were soon taught}}\n#* {{quote-book|yol|year=1867|chapter=A YOLA ZONG|number=8|page=86<ref name=Poole>{{R:Poole 1867}}</ref>\n|title=SONGS,"
  body " ETC. IN THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|passage='''Hi''' kinket an keilt, ee vewe aam 'twode snite.|translation='''They''' kicked and rolled, the few that appeared.}}\n# [[them]]\n#* {{quote-book|yol|"
  body "year=1927|chapter=ZONG OF TWI MAARKEET MOANS|line=7<ref>{{R:Browne 1927}}</ref>|page=129|title=THE ANCIENT DIALECT OF THE BARONIES OF FORTH AND BARGY, COUNTY WEXFORD|passage=Shu ztaared an shu ztudied"
  body " '''hi''' near parshagh moan,|translation=She stared and she studied ('''them''') by the other passive woman,}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n==Yoruba==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Pronunciati"
  body "on====\n{{yo-IPA|hí}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{yo-pos|noun|hí}}\n\n# {{Latn-def|yo|name|H|h}}\n\n====See also====\n{{list:Latin script letter names/yo}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* "
  body "{{alt|yo|sí}}\n\n====Preposition====\n{{yo-pos|preposition|hí}}\n\n# {{lb|yo|Ìkálẹ̀}} [[to]], [[at]], [[toward]] {{q|used when movement is implied}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|yo|húlí|t=to the "
  body "home}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|yo|ní}}\n\n==Zou==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{zom-IPA|hi}}\n* {{hyph|zom|hi}}\n\n====Particle====\n{{zom-particle|hi}}\n\n# [[yes]]\n# {{n-g|U"
  body "sed to mark a verbal phrase as [[affirmative]].}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{inh|zom|tbq-kuk-pro|*khlii}}.\n\n====Pronunciation 1====\n* {{zom-IPA|hi}}\n* {{hyph|zom|hi}}\n\n=====Noun=====\n{{zom-no"
  body "un|hi}}\n\n# [[tear]]\n\n====Pronunciation 2====\n* {{zom-IPA|hì}}\n* {{hyph|zom|hi}}\n\n=====Noun=====\n{{zom-noun|hì}}\n\n# [[drop]] {{gl|of water}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:zom:Thanglienmang:2010"
  body "|page=117}}\n\n{{C|zom|Bodily fluids}}""}}"

response_0021_api_php_action_parse_pag
  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=how_are_you&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "{""parse"":{""title"":""how are you"",""pageid"":35900,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""==English==\n{{phrasebook|en|Greetings}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|how're you||informal}}\n* {{alt|en|HRU||initia"
  body "lism}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/haʊ ˈɑː juː/|a=RP}}\n* {{IPA|en|/haʊ ˈɑɹ ju/|a=GA}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-how_are_you.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{IPA|en|/hæɔ ˈaː jʉː/|/hæɔ ˈaː jə/|a=AU}}\n** {{audio|en|"
  body "en-au-how_are_you.ogg|a=AU}}\n\n===Phrase===\n{{en-head|phr|head=?}}\n\n# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} An informal greeting, not requiring a literal response. In form a question, and thus followed by a questio"
  body "n mark. Typical responses include:\n#: {{ux|en|I'm very well, thank you. '''How are you'''? ''(formal)''<br>[[I'm fine, thank you]]. ''/'' <br> Fine, thanks. ''(informal) /'' <br> Fine, and you? ''(in"
  body "formal)''}}\n# {{lb|en|idiomatic|Ireland}} (Following a noun phrase; stress on ''are'') An expression of derision, that the preceding referent is unworthy of the name. In form of an exclamation, and t"
  body "hus often followed by an exclamation mark.\n#* '''1967''' July 20: [https://www.oireachtas.ie/en/debates/debate/dail/1967-07-20/26/ Questions. Oral Answers. — Free Travel for Old Age Pensioners.] ''Dá"
  body "il Éireann debates''\n#** [[w:Seán Dunne (politician)|Mr. Dunne]]: \""A small point\"", says the Minister for Justice.\n#** [[w:Richie Ryan (politician)|Mr. Ryan]]: Justice, '''how are you'''! He would "
  body "not recognise it in this world or the next.\n#* {{quote-journal|en|year=2013 December 31|url=https://www.independent.ie/regionals/goreyguardian/news/christmas-how-are-you-well-remember-this-one-for-a-"
  body "while-29877194.html|title='Christmas '''how are you'''! We'll remember this one for a while'\""|work=Gorey Guardian|passage='Christmas '''how are you'''!' exclaimed Jim O'Hanlon ruefully. 'We will reme"
  body "mber this one for quite a while anyway.' He was grateful that at least no one was injured in the incident.}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* ''(formal greeting)''\n** {{l|en|how do you do}}?\n* ''(informal gre"
  body "eting)''\n** {{l|en|how are you doing}}?\n** {{l|en|how's it going}}?, [[how's things]]?, [[how's tricks]]?, [[what's up]]? {{qualifier|more informal}}\n** {{l|en|how's it hanging}}? {{qualifier|slang"
  body "}}\n** See also [[Thesaurus:how are you]]\n* ''(expression of derision)''\n** {{l|en|my foot}}!, {{l|en|my eye}}!, {{l|en|my arse}}!, {{l|en|my ass}}!\n** {{l|en|indeed}}!\n\n====Translations====\n{{t"
  body "rans-top-see|greeting|how's it going|how}}\n* Abkhaz: {{t|ab|ушԥаҟоу}}, {{t|ab|бышԥаҟоу}}\n* Afrikaans: [[hoe gaan dit]]?\n* Ainu: {{t|ain|[[エイワンケ ア]]?|tr=eiwanke a?}}\n* Akan: {{t|ak|wo ho te sɛn}}\n"
  body "* Albanian: [[si jeni]]? {{qualifier|formal}}, [[qysh je]]? {{qualifier|informal}}\n*: Arbëresh Albanian: {{t|aae|si rrini|alt=si rrini?}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{t|aae|si rri|alt=si rri?}} {{qualifie"
  body "r|informal}}\n* American Sign Language: {{t|ase|BentB@BackFinger-PalmBack-BentB@CenterChesthigh-PalmBack C@Ulnar-PalmUp-C@CenterChesthigh-PalmUp 1@CenterChesthigh-TipFingerForward}}\n* Amharic: {{t|am"
  body "|እንደምን አለህ}} {{qualifier|to a male}}, {{t|am|እንደምን አለሽ}} {{qualifier|to a female}}, {{t|am|እንደምን አላችሁ|p}}\n* Apache:\n*: Jicarilla: {{t|apj|haʼáńsį}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|كَيْف الْحال؟}}, {{t+|ar|كَيْفَ "
  body "حَالُكَ؟}} {{qualifier|to a male, formal}}, {{t+|ar|كَيْف حَالَك؟}} {{qualifier|to a male, informal}}; {{t+|ar|كَيْفَ حَالُكِ؟}} {{qualifier|to a female, formal}}, {{t+|ar|كَيْف حَالِك؟}} {{qualifier|"
  body "to a female, informal}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|ازيك|alt=إِزَّيَّك؟|m|tr=izzáyyak?}} {{qualifier|to a male}}; {{t|arz|ازيك|alt=إِزَّيِّك؟|f|tr=izzáyyik?}} {{qualifier|to a female}}\n*: Hijazi Ara"
  body "bic: {{t|acw|كيفك|alt=كيفَك؟|m|tr=kēfak?}} {{qualifier|to a male}}; {{t|acw|كيفك|alt=كيفِك؟|f|tr=kēfik?}} {{qualifier|to a female}}\n*: Mesopotamian Arabic: {{t|apc|شْلُونَك؟|tr=šlōnak?|m}} {{qualifie"
  body "r|to a male}}; {{t|apc|شْلُونَك؟|tr=šlōnik?|f}}, {{t|apc|شْلُونَك؟|tr=šlōnič?|f}} {{qualifier|to a female}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{t|ary|لا باس؟|tr=lā bās?}}, {{t|ary|كي داير|tr=kī dāyer}} {{qualifier"
  body "|to a male}}, {{t|ary|كي دايرة|tr=kī dāyra}} {{qualifier|to a female}}, {{t|ary|كيف عامل|tr=kīf ʕāmel}} {{qualifier|to a male}}, {{t|ary|كيف عاملة|tr=kīf ʕāmla}} {{qualifier|to a female}}\n*: North Le"
  body "vantine Arabic: {{t|apc|كِيفَك؟|m|tr=kīfak?}} {{qualifier|to a male}}; {{t|apc|كِيفِك؟|m|tr=kīfik?}} {{qualifier|to a female}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{t|aii|ܕܐܟܝ ܝܘܬ|alt=ܕܵܐܟ݂ܝܼ ܝܘܸܬ؟}"
  body "} {{qualifier|to a male}}, {{t|aii|ܕܐܟܝ ܝܘܬܝ|alt=ܕܵܐܟ݂ܝܼ ܝܘܵܬܝ؟}} {{qualifier|to a female}}, {{t|aii|ܕܐܟܝ ܝܬܘܢ|alt=ܕܵܐܟ݂ܝܼ ܝܬܘܿܢ؟}} {{qualifier|to a group}}, {{t|aii|ܕܐܟܝ ܝܠܗ ܟܝܦܘܟ|alt=ܕܵܐܟ݂ܝܼ ܝܠܹܗ ܟܲ"
  body "ܝܦܘܼܟ݂؟}} {{qualifier|more formal; to a male}}, {{t|aii|ܐܝܟܢܐ ܟܐ ܚܙܝܬ ܢܦܫܘܟ|alt=ܐܲܝܟܲܢܵܐ ܟܹܐ ܚܵܙܹܝܬ ܢܲܦ̮ܫܘܼܟ݂؟}} {{qualifier|more formal; to a male}}\n*: Classical Syriac:\n* Arapaho: [[kooni'ííni]]?\"
  body "n* Armenian: {{t|hy|ինչպե՞ս ես}} {{qualifier|singular}}, {{t|hy|ո՞նց ես}} {{qualifier|singular}}, {{t|hy|ինչպե՞ս եք}} {{qualifier|polite or plural}}, {{t|hy|ո՞նց եք}} {{qualifier|polite or plural}}\n*"
  body " Assamese: {{t|as|আপোনাৰ ভালনে?}} {{q|formal}}, {{t|as|তোমাৰ ভালনে?}} {{q|familiar}}, {{t|as|তোৰ ভালনে?}} {{q|informal}}, {{t|as|আপুনি ভালে আছেনে?}} {{q|formal}}, {{t|as|তুমি ভালে আছানে?}} {{q|familia"
  body "r}}, {{t|as|তই ভালে আছনে?}} {{q|informal}}, {{t|as|কি খবৰ?}} {{q|familiar, informal}}, {{t|as|আপুনি কেনে আছে?}} {{q|formal}}, {{t|as|তুমি কেনে আছা?}} {{q|familiar}}, {{t|as|তই কেনে আছ?}} {{q|informal}"
  body "}\n* Asturian: {{t|ast|cómo tas}}, {{t|ast|qué faes}}\n* Atayal: {{t|tay|lokah su ga}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|necəsən|c}} {{qualifier|(informal)}}\n* Bashkir: {{t|ba|хәлдәр нисек?}}\n* Basque: {{t|eu|"
  body "zer moduz}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|як спра́вы?}}, {{t|be|як пажыва́еш?}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|be|як пажыва́еце?}} {{qualifier|formal or plural}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|আপনি কেমন আছেন?}} {{qualifier"
  body "|formal}}, {{t|bn|তুমি কেমন আছ?}} {{qualifier|familiar}}, {{t+|bn|তুই কেমন আছিস?}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Bikol:\n*: Central Bikol: {{t|bcl|kumusta na?}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|как си}}? {{qualifier|"
  body "informal}}, {{t|bg|как сте}}? {{qualifier|formal or plural}}\n* Burmese: {{t|my|နေကောင်းရဲ့လား။}}, {{t|my|နေကောင်းလား။}}\n* Catalan: {{t|ca|com estàs}}?, {{qualifier|formal}} {{t|ca|com està}}?, {{qua"
  body "lifier|informal}} {{t|ca|com va}}?\n* Cebuano: {{t|ceb|kumusta}}?, {{t|ceb|kumusta na ka}}?\n* Chamorro: {{t|ch|kao mamaolek ha' hao}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|ch|håfa tatatmanu hao}} {{qualifier|f"
  body "ormal}}\n* Chechen: {{t|ce|муха ду гӏуллакхаш?}}\n* Cherokee: {{t|chr|ᏙᎯᏧ?}}\n* Chichewa: {{t|ny|muli bwanji?}}\n* Chickasaw: {{t|cic|hallito chokma chinchokma}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t+|yue|你好"
  body "嗎|alt=你好嗎？|tr=nei5 hou2 maa3?}}\n*: Dungan: {{t|dng|задини?}}, {{t|dng|задигә?}}, {{t|dng|ни хо ма?}}, {{t|dng|ни җўди хома?}}\n*: Hakka: {{t|hak|你好冇|tr=ngì-hó-mò / nì-hó-mò / ǹ-hó-mò / ǹg-hó-mò}}\n*:"
  body " Hokkien: {{t|nan-hbl|[[汝]][[好勢]][[無]]？|tr=lí hó-sè--bô? / lír hó-sè--bô? / lú hó-sè--bô?}}, {{t|nan-hbl|你好無|alt=汝好無？|tr=lí hó--bô? / lír hó--bô? / lú hó--bô?}}, {{t|nan-hbl|[[汝]][[較]][[好]][[無]]？|tr=l"
  body "í khà hó--bô? / lír khà hó--bô? / lú khà hó--bô?}}, {{t|nan-hbl|[[汝]][[食]][[未]]？|tr=lí chia̍h bē? / lír chia̍h bēr? / lí chia̍h bōe? / lú chia̍h bōe? / lír chia̍h běr?}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|你好嗎|alt"
  body "=你好嗎？|tr=nǐhǎo ma?}} (''informal singular'')\n*: Wu: {{t|wuu|儂好𠲎？|tr=6non 5hau 0va}}\n* Chinook Jargon: {{t|chn|qʰata mayka}}\n* Choctaw: {{t|cho|chim achukma̱?}}\n* Circassian:\n*: West Circassian: {"
  body "{t|ady|дауэ ущыт?}}\n* Comorian:\n*: Ngazidja Comorian: {{t|zdj|haɓari ?}}, {{t|zdj|hufanyiha dje ?}}, {{t|zdj|ngawe dje ?}}, {{t|zdj|hukaantsi dje?}}\n* Cornish: {{t|kw|fatla genes}}\n* Crimean Tatar"
  body ": {{t|crh|nasılsıñız?}} {{qualifier|formal}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|jak se máš}}? (''informal singular''), {{t+|cs|jak se máte}}? {{qualifier|formal or plural}}\n* Dakota: {{t|dak|token yauŋ he?}}\n* Danis"
  body "h: {{t|da|hvordan har du det?}}, {{t+|da|hvordan går det?}}\n* Deori: {{t|der|dakiya chuina?}} {{q|formal}}, {{t|der|noi chuina?}} {{q|familiar}}\n* Dusun:\n*: Central Dusun: {{t|dtp|nunu kabar?}}\n* "
  body "Dutch: {{t|nl|hoe gaat het}}?, {{t|nl|hoe is het}}?, {{qualifier|informal}} {{t|nl|alles goed}}?\n* Esperanto: [[kiel vi fartas]]?\n* Estonian: {{t|et|kuidas läheb}}?, {{t|et|kuidas käsi käib?}} {{qua"
