  body "|ug|ياڭيۇ}}, {{t|ug|بەرەڭگە}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|kartoshka}}, {{t|uz|yerolma}}\n* Venetan: {{t+|vec|tartùfola|m}}, {{t+|vec|pomo de tèra|m}}, {{t|vec|patata|f}}\n* Veps: {{t|vep|kartohk}}, {{t|vep|kart"
  body "ofin}}, {{t|vep|mugulantoi paslön}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|khoai tây}}\n* Vilamovian: {{t|wym|aorpuł|m}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|pötet}}, {{qualifier|Solanum tuberosum}} {{t|vo|pötetaplan}}\n* Võro: {{t|v"
  body "ro|kardohkas}}\n* Votic: {{t|vot|maamuna}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|crompire|f}}, {{t+|wa|canada|m}}, {{t+|wa|truke|f}}, {{t+|wa|petote|f}}, {{t+|wa|cartoxhe|f}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|taten|f}}\n* Winnebago: {"
  body "{t|win|too}}\n* Wolof: {{t|wo|pombiteer}}\n* Xhosa: {{t|xh|itapile}}\n* Yakut: {{t|sah|хортуоппуй}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|קאַרטאָפֿל|m|f}}, {{t|yi|בולבע|f}}\n* Yoidik: {{t|ydk|sarembʌt}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|y"
  body "o|ọ̀dùnkún}}\n* Yup'ik: {{t|esu|patitussaaq}}, {{t|esu|kantuuvvilaq}}\n* Zhuang: {{t|za|majlingzsuz}}\n* Zulu: {{t+|zu|izambane|c5|c6}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n{{trans-top|underpowered computer}}\n* Chines"
  body "e:\n*: Mandarin: {{t|cmn|土豆服務器}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|peruna}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|kentang}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|patata|f}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Marathi: {{t-check|mr|अळु}}\n{{tr"
  body "ans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb|~es}}\n\n# {{lb|en|slang|transitive}} To [[hit]] very hard; to [[pummel]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2014|author=James Dixon; Arnold Furious; Bob Dahlstrom|title=T"
  body "he Raw Files: 1998|page=26\n|passage=Bradshaw doesn't find much humour in it though, and beats the tar out of Dustin, '''potatoing''' him with every blow.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To hit with a throw"
  body "n or fired potato.\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2017|author=A. J. Low|title=Sherlock Sam’s Orange Shorts: Special Edition\n|passage=Yvonne and Lee Swee '''potatoed''' Deputy Lestrade multiple times before"
  body " Sheriff Moran '''potatoed''' them both. {{...}} Suddenly, Sheriff Moran heard the ''click click'' of an empty weapon. He turned to see that both Mayor Eliza and Kat had run out of ammunition.}}\n\n=="
  body "=Interjection===\n{{en-intj}}\n\n# {{lb|en|onomatopoeia|often repeated}} The [[rhythmic]] [[sound]] produced by a [[V-twin]] engine—a distinctive [[deep]], [[throaty]] [[exhaust]] note.\n\n===Referenc"
  body "es===\n<references/>\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aooptt|patoot|topato}}\n\n{{cln|en|nouns with irregular plurals}}\n{{C|en|People|Potatoes}}\n\n==Ido==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{dercat|io|es|tnq}"
  body "}\n{{bor+|io|en|potato}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{io-IPA}}\n* {{rhymes|io|ato}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{io-noun|potat}}\n\n# [[#English|potato]]\n#: {{syn|io|terpomo}}\n\n{{C|io|Nightshades|Vegetables}}\n\"
  body "n==Italian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr}}\n\n===Participle===\n{{it-pp}}\n\n# {{past participle of|it|potare}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|it|a=aooptt|optato|topato}}\n\n==Latin==\n\n===Pronu"
  body "nciation===\n* {{la-IPA|pōtātō}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|la|verb form|head=pōtātō}}\n\n# {{inflection of|la|pōtō||2//3|s|futr|actv|impr}}\n\n===Participle===\n{{head|la|participle form|head=pōtātō}}\n\n"
  body "# {{infl of|la|pōtātus||mn|dat//abl|s}}""}}"

