  body "check|sv|jaså}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====References====\n<references/>\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{etymid|en|ally}}From {{affix|en|re-|ally}}.\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{alt form|en|re-ally}}.\n#"
  body "* {{quote-text|en|year=1917|title=German American Annals|page=69\n|passage=She wished since long to die and to be '''reallied''' with her children in heaven.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1997|author=War"
  body "ren F. Kuehl; Lynne Dunn|title=Keeping the Covenant: American Internationalists and the League of Nations, 1920-1939|page=19|publisher=Kent State University Press|isbn=9780873385664\n|passage=Followin"
  body "g the election, those who had publicly opposed Harding hastened to '''really''' themselves with Republicans who had remained in the party.}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aellry|rallye|y'all're"
  body "|yaller}}\n\n{{cln|en|degree adverbs|intensifiers|modal adverbs|sarcastic terms|speech-act adverbs}}""}}"

response_0031_api_php_action_parse_pag
  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=regards&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "{""parse"":{""title"":""regards"",""pageid"":229709,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""==English==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ɹɪˈɡɑɹdz/|a=GenAm}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ɹɪˈɡɑːdz/|a=RP}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-regards.ogg"
  body "|a=US}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɑː(ɹ)dz|s=2}}\n* {{hyphenation|en|re|gards}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|en|noun form}}\n\n# {{plural of|en|regard}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|p}}\n\n# Good wishes.\n## A [[greeting]] "
  body "to pass on to another person.\n##: {{ux|en|Give my '''regards''' to your brother when you next see him.}}\n## A greeting at the end of a letter or e-mail communication.\n##: {{ux|en|'''Regards''', Joh"
  body "n.'' ''Kind '''regards''', Peter.}}\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alter|en|regds.||abbreviation}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col2|en|as regards|best regards|in regards to|kind regards|kindest reg"
  body "ards|warm regards|warmest regards|with regards to}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|greeting to pass to another person}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|تَحِيَّة|f}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|прывіта́нне|n}}, {{t"
  body "+|be|віта́нне|n}}, {{t|be|прыве́т|m}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|records|m-p}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|問候|tr=wènhòu}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|groeten|p}} or {{t+|nl|groetjes|p}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|terv"
  body "eiset|p}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|respects|m-p}}\n* Galician: {{t|gl|saúdos|m-p}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Gruß|m}}, {{t+|de|Grüße|m-p}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|דְּרִישַׁת שָׁלוֹם|tr=drishát shalóm}}\n* Hungarian: {{"
  body "t+|hu|üdvözlet}}, {{t|hu|jókívánságok|p}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|kveðja}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|よろしく|tr=yoroshiku}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|안부(安否)}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|hilsen}}\n* Persian: {{t"
  body "|fa|ملاحظات}}, {{t+|fa|سلام|tr=salâm}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|pozdrowienie|n-p|alt=pozdrowienia}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|lembranças|f-p}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|приве́т|m}}, {{t+|ru|покло́н|m}}, {{t+|ru|прив"
  body "е́тствие|n}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|saludos|m-p}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|hälsningar}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|віта́ння|n}}, {{t+|uk|приві́т|m}}, {{t|uk|привіта́ння|n}}, {{t|uk|віта́ння|n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\"
  body "n{{trans-top|greeting at the end of a letter}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|مَعَ تَحِيَّاتِي}}, {{t|ar|مَعَ تَمَنِّيَّاتِي}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t|cmn|[[祝]][[好]]|tr=zhù hǎo}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|hilsen}}\"
  body "n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|groeten|p}} or {{t+|nl|groetjes|p}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|terveisin|p}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|cordialement}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|საუკეთესო სურვილებით}}\n* German: {{t|de|mit freundlichen "
  body "Grüßen}}, {{t|de|viele Grüße}}, {{t|de|beste Grüße}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|χαιρετισμούς|m-p}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|בברכה|tr=biv'rakhá}}\n* Hungarian: {{t|hu|üdvözlettel}}, {{t+|hu|tisztelettel}}, {{t|hu|szív"
  body "élyes üdvözlettel}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|kveðja}}\n* Italian: {{t|it|cordiali saluti}}\n* Japanese: {{t|ja|よろしくお願いします|tr=よろしくおねがいしま​す, yoroshiku onegai shimasu}}, {{t+|ja|よろしく|tr=yoroshiku}}\n* Norwe"
  body "gian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|hilsen}}\n* Polish: {{t|pl|pozdrawiam}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|cordialmente}}, {{t+|pt|com}} {{t+|pt|apreço}}\n* Russian: {{t|ru|всех благ}}, {{t+|ru|всего́ до́брого}}, {{t+|r"
  body "u|всего́ хоро́шего}}, {{t|ru|с тёплыми пожела́ниями}}, {{t|ru|с наилу́чшими пожела́ниями}},\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|s pozdravom}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|saludos}}, {{t|es|saludos cordiales}}, {{t+|es|cordialme"
  body "nte}}, {{t|es|saludos cariñosos|m-p}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|hälsningar}}\n* Thai: {{t|th|ขอแสดงความนับถือ|tr=kɔ̌ɔ-sà-dɛɛng-kwaam-náp-tʉ̌ʉ}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|en|verb form}}\n\n# {{"
  body "infl of|en|regard||s-verb-form}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=adegrrs|Dragers|graders|red rags|redrags}}\n\n{{cln|en|2-syllable words|phrasebook}}\n\n==Cebuano==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der"
  body "|ceb|en|regards}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{hyph|ceb|re|gards}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|ceb|verb}}\n\n# to give one's regards\n\n===Interjection===\n{{head|ceb|interjection}}\n\n# my regards\n\n==Fre"
  body "nch==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-0x010C-regards.wav}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|fr|noun form|g=m}}\n\n# {{plural of|fr|regard}}""}}"

response_0032_api_php_action_parse_pag
  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=spa&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "{""parse"":{""title"":""spa"",""pageid"":71723,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""{{also|Appendix:Variations of \""spa\""}}\n==Translingual==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{clip|mul|en:'''Spa'''nish,es:e'''spa'''ñol}}.\n\n===Sy"
  body "mbol===\n{{mul-symbol}}\n\n# {{ISO 639|2&3|Spanish language|Spanish}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{langcat|es}}\n\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{ety|en|Spa}}\nThe term is derived from the name"
  body " of the Belgian town of [[w:Spa, Belgium|Spa]], where since medieval times illnesses caused by iron deficiency were treated by drinking [[chalybeate]] (iron-bearing) spring water. In 16<sup>th</sup> c"
  body "entury [[England]] the old Roman ideas of medicinal bathing were revived at towns like Bath, and in 1571 William Slingsby who had been to the Belgian town (which he called ''Spaw'') discovered a chaly"
  body "beate spring in [[Yorkshire]]. He built an enclosed well at what became known as [[Harrogate]], the first resort in England for drinking medicinal waters, then in 1596 Dr. Timothy Bright called the re"
  body "sort ''The English Spaw'', beginning the use of the word ''Spa'' as a generic description rather than as the place name of the Belgian town. At first this term referred specifically to resorts for wat"
  body "er drinking rather than bathing, but this distinction was gradually lost and many ''spas'' offer external remedies.\n\nThere are various stories about the origin of the name. A Belgian spring of iron-"
  body "bearing water was called ''Espa'' from the {{der|en|wa|-}} term for \""fountain\"", and was used in 1326 as a cure by an iron master with such success that he founded a health resort that developed into"
  body " the town, though it has been suggested that this term may be derived from the name of the resort. Some have suggested that the town's name can be ultimately sourced from {{der|en|la|spargō|spargere|t"
  body "=to scatter, sprinkle, or moisten}}, though this derivation is problematic.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈspɑː/|a=RP}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈspɔː/|a=UK,obsolete|ref={{R:Jespersen MEGoHP|I|10.571|303"
  body "}}}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈspɑ/|a=GA}}\n** {{audio|en|En-us-spa.oga|a=US}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈspɐː/|a=AU}}\n** {{audio|en|En-au-spa.ogg|a=AU}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈspa/|a=Scotland}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɑː|s=1}}\n* {{homophone"
  body "s|en|spar|aa=non-rhotic}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# A health [[resort]] near a mineral [[spring]] or [[hot spring]].\n# A [[trendy]] or [[fashionable]] resort.\n# A [[health club]].\n#: {{ux|e"
  body "n|They went to a '''spa''' for a massage.}}\n# A [[hot tub]].\n#: {{ux|en|Their bath is fitted  with a '''spa'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|Rhode Island|Massachusetts|Maine}} A [[convenience store]].\n\n=====Synon"
  body "yms=====\n* {{l|en|health club}}\n* {{l|en|resort}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|medispa|spa-goer|spalike|spathroom|spool||dental spa|spa cuisine|spagoer|health spa\n|Croft Spa\n|Boston Spa\n|"
  body "Droitwich Spa\n|Leamington Spa\n|spa bath\n|spa pool\n|spa town\n|spa water|Woodhall Spa}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|health resort near a mineral spring or hot spring}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|"
  body "sq|llixhë|f}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|مُنْتَجَع|m}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|溫泉|tr=wēnquán}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|banejo}}, {{t|eo|banloko}}, {{t|eo|termoj|p}}, {{t|eo|varmobanejo}}, {{t|eo|termob"
  body "anejo}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kylpylä}}, {{t+|fi|spa}}\n* French: {{t|fr|ville d'eau|f}}, {{t+|fr|spa|m}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|სპა}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Kurort|m}}, {{t+|de|Bad|n}}, {{t|de|Heilbad|n}}\n* "
  body "Hebrew: {{t+|he|סְפָּא|m|tr=spa}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|gyógyfürdő}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|termo}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|terme|f-p}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|温泉|tr=おんせん, onsen}}, {{t+|ja|スパ|tr=supa}}\n* Khmer: {{"
  body "t|km|ស្ប៉ា}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|aquae|f-p}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|spa|n}}, {{t+|pl|uzdrowisko|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|spa|m}}\n* Russian: {{qualifier|indeclinable}} {{t+|ru|спа|n}}, {{qualifier|Japanes"
  body "e style}} {{t+|ru|онсэ́н|m}}, {{t|ru|лече́бный исто́чник|m}}, {{t+|ru|ба́ня|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|spa|m}}, {{t+|es|balneario|m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|hälsobrunn|c}}, {{t+|sv|spa|n}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|"
  body "tr|ılıca}}, {{t+|tr|kaplıca}}, {{t+|tr|kudret hamamı}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|ایلیجه|tr=ılıca}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|sba|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|trendy or fashionable resort}}\n* German"
  body ": {{t+|de|Therme|f}}, {{t|de|Saunapark|m}}, {{t+|de|Spa|n|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n=====See also=====\n{{col|en\n|caldarium\n|pump room\n|sanatorium\n|take the waters\n|wellness hotel\n}}\n\n===Etymol"
  body "ogy 2===\nShortened form of {{m|en|spastic}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|en|/spɑː/}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɑː|s=1}}\n{{rfap|en|Ireland|variety=Ireland}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|en|Irelan"
  body "d|slang}} An idiot; a [[gobshite]]\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2010|author=Paul Murray|title=[https://books.google.com/books?id=8CI5XhzjSHEC&pg=PT808 Skippy Dies]|isbn=9780141943893\n|passage=What the fu"
  body "ck was she talking about, he must think she's such a '''spa'''.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2018|author=Rachael English|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5-9XEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT42|title=The Night of the"
  body " Party\n|passage=['...] We'll say it was just the two of us sitting in the shed having a chat.'<br>'Don't be such a '''spa'''. Nobody will believe we were sitting in the shed having a chat.[...']}}\n#"
  body " {{lb|en|Ireland|slang}} A clumsy person (see [[spastic]])\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1993|author=Roddy Doyle|title=Paddy Clarke Ha Ha Ha|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/paddyclarkehahah00rodd_0/pag"
  body "e/17/|page=17|isbn=0-7493-9735-7\n|passage=— Hit it.<br>He missed.<br>— You're a big '''spa''', I told him.}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aps|APS|SAP|sap|AP"
  body "s|Psa.|PsA|s.ap.|asp|pas|Pas|PSA|ASP|PAs|PAS}}\n\n{{cln|en|heteronyms|terms derived from toponyms}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/spaː/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-spa.ogg}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|a"
  body "ː|s=1}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom earlier {{m|nl|spade}}, from {{inh|nl|dum|spade}}, from {{inh|nl|odt|*spado}}, from {{inh|nl|gem-pro|*spadô}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alt|nl|spade}}\n\n=="
  body "==Noun====\n{{nl-noun|m|spaden|+}}\n\n# [[spade]]\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom the ''Spa'' brand of mineral water, which originates from the Belgian town of {{m|fr|Spa}}. The compound {{m|nl|spawater}} "
  body "is attested as early as the 17th century, however.\n\n====Noun====\n{{nl-noun|m|-'s|+}}\n\n# [[mineral water]]\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|nl\n|spa blauw\n|spa rood\n}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\n{{r"
  body "oot|nl|ine-pro|*speh₁-}}\nFrom earlier {{m|nl|spade}}, from {{inh|nl|dum|spade}}, from {{inh|nl|odt|*spādi}}, from {{inh|nl|gem-pro|*spēdiz}}. Cognate with {{cog|de|spät}}.\n\n====Alternative forms==="
  body "=\n* {{alt|nl|spade}}\n\n====Adjective====\n{{nl-adj|spader|spaadst}}\n\n# {{lb|nl|obsolete}} [[late]]\n#: {{syn|nl|laat}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{nl-decl-adj|spade|part=spaads}}\n\n{{cln|nl|generi"
  body "cized trademarks}}\n\n==Norwegian Nynorsk==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|nn|spada}}\n* {{alt|nn|spade}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom the noun {{l|nn|spade}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|no|/spɑ"
  body "ː/}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|nn|verb|present tense|spar|past tense|spadde|past participle|spadd|or|spadt|present participle|spadande|imperative|spa}}\n\n# to use a spade or shovel, to [[dig]], to [[shov"
  body "el]]\n\n===References===\n* {{R:nn:OB}}\n\n==Piedmontese==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|pms|/spa/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|pms|noun|g=f|plural|spe}}\n\n# [[sword]]\n\n==Polish==\n{{wp|pl:[[+ (terape"
  body "utyka)|+]]}}\n[[File:Therme Vals outdoor pool, Vals, Graubünden, Switzerland - 20090809.jpg|thumb|spa]]\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|pl|SPA|SpA}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|pl|:ubor|en:spa|text="
  body "+|tree=1}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|a=LL-Q809 (pol)-Olaf-spa.wav|hh=Spa}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pl-noun|n|indecl=1}}\n\n# {{l|en|spa}} {{gl|beauty treatments designed to moisturise and nourish the s"
  body "kin; also: cosmetics used for such treatments}}\n# {{l|en|spa}} {{gl|health resort near a mineral spring or hot spring}}\n#: {{hyper|pl|bad|kurort|uzdrowisko|zdrojowisko}}\n# {{l|en|spa}} {{gl|hot tub"
  body "}}\n#: {{syn|pl|jacuzzi}}\n#: {{hyper|pl|wanna}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{pl-adj|-|adv=-}}\n\n# {{lb|pl|postpositive}} {{l|en|spa}} {{gl|beauty treatments designed to moisturise and nourish the skin; als"
  body "o: cosmetics used for such treatments}}\n# {{lb|pl|postpositive}} {{l|en|spa}} {{gl|hot tub}}\n#: {{syn|pl|jacuzzi}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pl:WSJP|spa I|56636}}\n* {{R:pl:WSJP|spa II|91735}}"
  body "\n* {{R:pl:PWN}}\n\n{{C|pl|Bathing|Cosmetics|Health|Places|Recreation}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|pt|en|spa}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pt-IPA}}\n* {{hyph|pt|spa}}\n\n===Noun===\n{"
  body "{pt-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|spa}} {{gloss|health resort near a spring}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pt:Aulete}}\n* {{R:pt:Priberam}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|es|en|spa}}.\n\n===Pronu"
  body "nciation===\n{{es-pr|espá}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|spa}}\n#: {{syn|es|balneario}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n{{es-unadapted}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DRAE}}\n\n{{cln|es|terms"
  body " derived from toponyms}}\n\n==Swedish==\n{{wp|sv:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom the name of the Belgian town of [[w:Spa, Belgium|Spa]]. {{etydate|1993}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|n}}\n\n# {{l|en|spa}} {{"
  body "gl|health resort with (hot) baths, and various treatments}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-noun-irreg-n|spa|[[spat]], [[spaet]]|span|spana|6=[[spats]], [[spaets]]}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|sv\n|s"
  body "paanläggning\n|spaavdelning\n|spahotell\n|spaweekend\n|spabehandling\n}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:svenska.se}}""}}"

response_0033_api_php_action_parse_pag
  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=tagger&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "{""parse"":{""title"":""tagger"",""pageid"":56679,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""==English==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈtæɡə(ɹ)/}}\n* {{audio|en|En-au-tagger.ogg|a=AU}}\n* {{rhymes|en|æɡə(ɹ)|s=2}}\n\n=="
  body "=Etymology 1===\n{{ety|en|:af|tag|-er|text=+|tree=1}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# One who or that which [[tag]]s.\n## The player who tries to catch others in the game of tag.\n##* {{quote-text|e"
  body "n|year=1989|author=Francis Edward Abernethy|title=Texas Toys and Games|page=111\n|passage=The teacher then calls on each one of the tagged to identify his '''tagger'''. If a student cannot guess corre"
  body "ctly, he must sit down.}}\n## A person who writes [[graffiti]] using a specific mark\n## {{lb|en|comptheory}} A [[program]] or [[algorithm]] that adds [[tag]]s for purposes of [[categorization]], e.g."
  body " grammatical information to words in a document, or genres to songs in a music collection.\n##* {{quote-journal|en|year=2018|author=Clarence Green; James Lambert|title=Advancing disciplinary literacy "
  body "through English for academic purposes: Discipline-specific wordlists, collocations and word families for eight secondary subjects|journal=Journal of English for Academic Purposes|volume=35|doi=https:/"
  body "/doi.org/10.1016/j.jeap.2018.07.004|page=109|text=To include part-of-speech (POS) information, the corpus was tagged using the CLAWS '''tagger'''.}}\n# A device for removing [[taglock]]s from [[sheep]"
  body "].<ref>{{R:Knight AMD}}</ref>\n# That which is pointed like a tag.\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1689|author=w:Charles Cotton|title=Burlesque\n|passage=hedgehogs' or porcupines' small '''taggers'''}}\n\n=="
  body "===Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|price tagger|tagger-along}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|person who writes graffiti}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|tagueur|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{"
  body "{rfe|en|Variant of [[tadger]]?}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|en|slang}} The [[penis]].<!--in Esquire. London: The National Magazine Company Ltd, 1992-->\n\n===Etymology 3===\n{{rfe|en}}\n\n"
  body "====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|en|in the plural}} [[sheet|Sheets]] of [[tin]] or other [[plate]] which run below the [[gauge]].<ref>{{R:Knight AMD}}</ref>\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n=="
  body "=Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aeggrt|garget}}\n\n{{C|en|Genitalia|People}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|fr|taguer}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fr|:bor|en:tag}}\n{{bor+|fr|en|tag}"
  body "}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|taguer}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-tagger.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Lyokoï-tagger.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n* {{"
  body "audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Jérémy-Günther-Heinz Jähnick-tagger.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Somain>>)}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{fr-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|fr|graffiti}} to [[tag#Verb|tag]]\n# to [[tag]] {{gloss|label}}\n#: {{ux"
  body "i|fr|tagger quelqu'un sur Facebook|tag someone on Facebook}}\n\n====Conjugation====\n{{fr-conj-auto|type=er|pron=taguer}}<!-- not a -ger verb; hence 'nous taggons' not 'nous taggeons' -->""}}"

response_0034_api_php_action_parse_pag
  url "https://en.wiktionary.org/w/api.php?action=parse&page=thank_you&prop=wikitext&formatversion=2&format=json&redirects=1"
  body "{""parse"":{""title"":""thank you"",""pageid"":6449,""redirects"":[],""wikitext"":""{{also|thankyou|thank-you}}\n==English==\n{{phrasebook|en}}\n{{was wotd|2016|November|24}}\n[[File:Thank You (13824254433).jpg|th"
  body "umb|A “thank you” sign being held up at a [[conference]] in [[Taiwan]] in 2014]]\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|thanke yow}}; as with {{m|en|thank God}}, {{m|en|praise be to God}}, and {{m|en|p"
  body "raise the Lord}}, it was originally a [[present subjunctive]] form but is usually not parsed that way in current usage. It has also sometimes been parsed as a [[prodrop]] form of ([[present indicative"
  body "]]) ''I thank you'', a mechanism that may plausibly coexist with the other one (instances being variable).\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{a|en|non-æ-tensing}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈθæŋk ˌju/|[ˈθæŋk ˌjʊu̯]}}\n**"
  body "* {{audio|en|En-uk-thank you.ogg|a=RP}}\n*** {{audio|en|en-au-thank you.ogg|a=AU}}\n**** {{a|en|th-fronting}}\n***** {{IPA|en|/ˈfæŋk ˌju/|[ˈfæŋk ˌjʊu̯]|a=UK}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈðæŋk ˌju/|[ˈðæŋk ˌjʊu̯]}}\"
  body "n* {{a|en|æ-tensing}}\n** {{a|en|US|CA}}\n*** {{IPA|en|/ˈθeɪ̯ŋk ˌju/|[ˈθeɪ̯ŋk ˌjʊu̯]}}\n**** {{audio|en|En-us-thank you 1.ogg|a=non-<<th-stopping>>}}\n**** {{audio|en|En-us-thank you 2.ogg|a=th-stoppi"
  body "ng}}\n*** {{IPA|en|/ˈðeɪ̯ŋk ˌju/|[ˈðeɪ̯ŋk ˌjʊu̯]}}\n* {{hyph|en|thank|you}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{en-intj}}\n\n# {{non-gloss|An expression of [[gratitude]] or [[politeness]] in response to somethin"
  body "g done or given.}} {{defdate|from c. 1400}}\n#: {{ux|en|“'''Thank you'''!” said the girl after her mom gave her a gift.}}\n#: {{ux|en|“And '''thank ''you''''' for being so sweet,” replied her mom.}}\n"
  body "#* {{quote-book|en|author=attributed to [[w:John Fletcher (playwright)|John Fletcher]]|chapter=[[w:Bonduca|Bonduca, a Tragedy]]|title=The Works of Mr. {{w|Francis Beaumont}}, and Mr. John Fletcher|loc"
  body "ation=London|publisher=Printed for {{w|Jacob Tonson}}, at Shakespear's Head over-against Catherine-street in the [[w:Strand, London|Strand]]|year=1711|volume=IV|section=act I, scene ii|page=2194|pageu"
  body "rl=https://books.google.com/books?id=3xFEAQAAMAAJ&pg=RA4-PA96|oclc=642500453|passage=''Jun''[''ius''] {{...}} The General has new Wine, new come over. / He muſt have new Acquaintance for it too, / For"
  body " I will ''none, I '''thank ye'''.'' / ''Pet''[''ilus''] ''None, I '''thank ye'''?'' / A short and touchy answer. ''None, I '''thank ye''''': / Ye do not scorn it, do ye?}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|autho"
  body "r=“G.”|title=The Dukedom (from ‘The News of Literature and Fashion, Science and Art.’)|journal=The Spirit of the Times; or, Essence of the Periodicals; Concentrating Every Week, All that is Worthy (as"
  body " Strictly Regarding the Time) of Being Preserved, from the Whole of Our Newspapers, Magazines, &c.|location=London|publisher=Printed by Milne, Banfield, and Duckworth [...] for J. Scott|date=22 April "
  body "1826|volume=I|issue=XXIX|page=436, column 1|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=JhAbAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA436|oclc=68226152|passage=I had some faint recollection of having a penny-piece in my waistcoat "
  body "pocket, and, pleased with the service he had rendered to us, I gave it him as his guerdon. \""'''Thank ye''', sir—'''thank ye''', sir—'''thank ye''', sir,\"" he cried, and immediately returned to his st"
  body "ation near the footway.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=w:Virginia Woolf|title=[[w:Mrs Dalloway|Mrs. Dalloway]]|location=London|publisher=[[w:Leonard Woolf|Leonard]] & {{w|Virginia Woolf}} at the {{w|Hog"
  body "arth Press}}|date=14 May 1925|oclc=1816789|passage=\""But, '''thank you''', Lucy, oh, '''thank you''',\"" said Mrs. Dalloway, and '''thank you''', '''thank you''', she went on saying (sitting down on th"
  body "e sofa with her dress over her knees, her scissors, her silks), '''thank you''', '''thank you''', she went on saying in gratitude to her servants generally for helping her to be like this, to be what "
  body "she wanted, gentle, generous-hearted.}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|author=w:Benny Andersson; w:Björn Ulvaeus|title=w:Thank You for the Music|album={{w|ABBA: The Album}}|artist=w:ABBA|date=12 December 1977|pa"
  body "ssage='''Thank you''' for the music, the songs I'm singing / Thanks for all the joy they're bringing / Who can live without it, I ask in all honesty / What would life be? / Without a song or a dance w"
  body "hat are we? / So I say '''thank you''' for the music / For giving it to me}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Bill Boyd|chapter=Striking a Deal|title=Stepdaddy: A Creative Memoir|location=Macon, Ga.|publish"
  body "er=w:Mercer University Press|year=2002|page=96|isbn=978-0-86554-781-0|passage='''Thank ya''', ma'am, '''thank ya''', '''thank ya''', '''thank ya'''. He's a good dog. He likes ever'body. He won' be no "
  body "bother. '''Thank ya''', ma'am, '''thank ya''', '''thank ya'''.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Jerry Goodwin|chapter=Thank You|title=Thank You: One of Seventeen Rules&nbsp;…: Wonderful for Men and Women "
  body "of All Ages|location=[Philadelphia, Pa.]|publisher=w:Xlibris|year=2007|page=19|isbn=978-1-4257-4126-6|passage=Always say \""'''thank you'''.\"" When in doubt, say \""'''thank you'''.\"" Say \""'''thank you"
  body "'''\"" even if you think it is not necessary in the circumstances. Whether the recipient thinks it is or is not, it will be appreciated and remembered. It is impossible to say \""'''thank you'''\"" too o"
  body "ften!}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Colin McEvoy; Lynn Olanoff|chapter=13|title=Fatal Jealousy: The True Story of a Doomed Romance, a Singular Obsession, and a Quadruple Murder|series=St. Martin's True"
  body " Crime Library|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=[[w:St. Martin's Press|St. Martin's Paperbacks]]|month=February|year=2014|page=136|isbn=978-1-250-00971-5|passage=His return text came about an hour la"
